TITLE: Setting Time Scale Options Individually in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set time scale options separately for border color and bar spacing. The barSpacing property adjusts the width of bars, effectively controlling the horizontal zoom level of the chart.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tradingview/lightweight-charts/blob/master/website/tutorials/customization/time-scale.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Setting the border color for the horizontal axis
chart.timeScale().applyOptions({
    borderColor: '#71649C',
});

// highlight-start
// Adjust the starting bar width (essentially the horizontal zoom)
chart.timeScale().applyOptions({
    barSpacing: 10,
});
// highlight-end
```

