TITLE: Implementing Safe Canvas Context Handling with Save/Restore Pattern
DESCRIPTION: Demonstration of best practices for rendering functions by using save/restore with try/finally blocks to ensure the canvas context state is properly maintained even if errors occur. This pattern should be used for any additional rendering functions within the coordinate space methods.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tradingview/lightweight-charts/blob/master/website/docs/plugins/canvas-rendering-target.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function myRenderingFunction(scope) {
    const ctx = scope.context;

    // save the current state of the context to the stack
    ctx.save();

    try {
        // example code
        scope.context.beginPath();
        scope.context.rect(0, 0, scope.mediaSize.width, scope.mediaSize.height);
        scope.context.fillStyle = 'rgba(100, 200, 50, 0.5)';
        scope.context.fill();
    } finally {
        // restore the saved context from the stack
        ctx.restore();
    }
}

target.useMediaCoordinateSpace(scope => {
    myRenderingFunction(scope);
    myOtherRenderingFunction(scope);
    /* ... */
});
```

